LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE SENATE
SENATE BILL NO. 1029
BY JUDICIARY AND RULES COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO JUDICIAL DISTRICTS; AMENDING SECTION 1-808, IDAHO CODE, TO RE-
3 VISE PROVISIONS REGARDING THE NUMBER OF JUDGES IN THE SEVENTH JUDICIAL
4 DISTRICT; AND DECLARING AN EMERGENCY AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.
5 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
6 SECTION 1. That Section 1-808, Idaho Code, be, and the same is hereby
7 amended to read as follows:
8 1-808. SEVENTH DISTRICT -- NUMBER OF JUDGES -- RESIDENT CHAMBERS. (1)
9 The seventh judicial district shall consist of the counties of Lemhi,
10 Custer, Butte, Clark, Fremont, Jefferson, Madison, Teton, Bonneville and
11 Bingham.
12 (2) The seventh judicial district shall have six (6) seven (7) district
13 judges.
14 (3) Resident chambers of the district judges of the seventh judicial
15 district shall be established as follows:
16 (a) One (1) resident chambers shall be established in Madison County;
17 (b) One (1) resident chambers shall be established in Bingham County;
18 (c) Three (3) Four (4) resident chambers shall be established in Bon-
19 neville County;
20 (d) One (1) resident chambers shall be established in Jefferson County.
21 SECTION 2. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
22 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after
23 July 1, 2025.

